<br>
There is no contradiction, Lurikeen.  I shall re-write it for you to make it more clear.<br>
<br>
I personally believe you recieve the spirit when you accept Christ.  I have deduced this from study on my own, in my church, and in biblical classes.  <br>
<br>
However, I do not believe that we as humans can KNOW one has the spirit unless we have the ability to look into men's hearts.  Which we cannot do, as we are not God.<br>
<br>
The difference is inherent in the wording : believe and know.<br>
<br>
To be even more clear:  When I speak of knowing - I mean KNOW beyond all doubt.  We cannot KNOW (which you have stated before) because we cannot prove it.  <br>
<br>
However, I personally do believe the spirit enters when I stated it did, upon accepting Christ, whether or not there are ANY outward manifestations.<br>
<br>
I hope that clears it up.<br>
<br>
There was no contradiction.<br>
