<br>
Again, this was not intended to be directed at you personally, Lurikeen.  When I wrote &quot;you&quot; in the above statement, I should have said &quot;one.&quot;  Please read the re -written statement.<br>
<br>
This is what I meant (I hope this is clear):<br>
<br>
On the subject of forgiveness: my point is that forgiveness is NOT a feeling one has necessarily (though that may be the case), but instead is an act that one does consciously.  In turn, by consciously forgiving someone, one then experience the feeling of forgivness.  <br>
<br>
I hope that is better?  What I intended to point out is that often people (in general) will forgive only if they feel like forgiving.  If you forgive whether you feel like it nor not, generally, the feeling of forgiveness will follow.<br>
<br>
My apology in my careless use of the pronoun &quot;you&quot; in my original statement.<br>
