<br>
As a christian, I tend to have tunnel vision when views of faith are called into play. It is refreshing to hear others disseminate ideas in a non-abusive manor (unlike most other religious debates). Towards the end it seemed to have some discussion of the existence of God and which religion was the truthful interpretation of the Deity.<br>
<br>
While none can offer absolute proof, we each make our decision and wonder why the other cannot see our point of view. With this in mind, after reading through all the posts, I found an old article from my astronomy clubs newsletter and thought I would share it. Please take this as only a new proposition to consider not one to be proved or disproved. Food for thought, or a long winded bump  <br>
